# Change discipline (small diffs)

## Default posture
- Make the **smallest** change that satisfies the request.
- Avoid drive-by refactors/renames/reformatting unless explicitly requested.
- Prefer incremental, reviewable diffs over ‚Äúbig bang‚Äù rewrites.

## When exploring vs changing
- If asked to investigate, stay read-only and report findings only.
- If asked to change code, keep scope tight to the requested behavior.

## Plan ‚Üí implement ‚Üí verify
- For any non-trivial change: produce a brief plan, list expected file touches, and a test plan.
- Before concluding work: run the **relevant** tests/checks and report exactly what was run + outcome.

## Guardrails
- Never add secrets to the repo (keys, tokens, creds, customer data).
- No production behavior changes unless explicitly approved.
